<subSubSection id="7AAE657C335AFFC5FF5EF990FCA2F8FB" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="320B36F7335AFFC5FF5EF990FCA2F8FB" blockId="11.[151,1437,1358,1888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="00C0EAE5335AFFC5FF5EF990FEA0F913" bold="true" box="[199,314,1646,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. One of the most advanced genera of 
<taxonomicName id="F5B44D74335AFFC5FD68F990FC4CF913" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" box="[753,982,1646,1672]" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
with an extremely deeply excavate and strongly enlarged, often transverse gonopodal coxites that form together a very prominent gonocoel cavity which conceals and protects usually rather complex, subtransverse and medially swollen telopodites, uni- to tripartite (including a more or less distinct, mesal, solenomere branch), held parallel to each other (
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FB0EF924FACBF96F" author="Golovatch, S. I." box="[1175,1361,1754,1780]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="207 - 226" refId="ref7882" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1992) Review of the Neotropical fauna of the millipede family Fuhrmannodesmidae, with the description of four new species from near Manaus, Central Amazonia, Brazil (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Amazoniana, 12 (2), 207 - 226." type="journal article" year="1992">Golovatch 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FAC4F924FA02F96F" author="Golovatch, S. I." box="[1373,1432,1754,1780]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="131 - 161" refId="ref7934" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1994) Further new Fuhrmannodesmidae from the environs of Manaus, Central Amazonia, Brazil, with a revision of Cryptogonodesmus Silvestri, 1898 (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Amazoniana, 13 (1 - 2), 131 - 161." type="journal article" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FF0EF900FF49F883" author="Golovatch, S. I." box="[151,211,1790,1816]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="27 - 30" refId="ref8039" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (2001) Two new polydesmoid millipedes from a whitesand forest area near Manaus, Central Amazonia, Brazil (Diplopoda: Polydesmida: Pyrgodesmidae, Fuhrmannodesmidae). Arthropoda Selecta, 10 (1), 27 - 30. [https: // kmkjournals. com / upload / PDF / ArthropodaSelecta / 10 / 10 _ 1 % 20027 _ 030 % 20 Golovatch. pdf]" type="journal article" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
). This condition is deemed to represent one of the most advanced in the gonopodal evolution of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="F5B44D74335AFFC5FF0EF8DCFEE6F8A7" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" box="[151,380,1826,1852]" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
compared to the developments observed in most of the remaining eight genera that occur in the region (
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FF74F8B8FE3CF8FB" author="Golovatch, S. I." box="[237,422,1862,1888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="207 - 226" refId="ref7882" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1992) Review of the Neotropical fauna of the millipede family Fuhrmannodesmidae, with the description of four new species from near Manaus, Central Amazonia, Brazil (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Amazoniana, 12 (2), 207 - 226." type="journal article" year="1992">Golovatch 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FE28F8B8FE76F8FB" author="Golovatch, S. I." box="[433,492,1862,1888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="131 - 161" refId="ref7934" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1994) Further new Fuhrmannodesmidae from the environs of Manaus, Central Amazonia, Brazil, with a revision of Cryptogonodesmus Silvestri, 1898 (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Amazoniana, 13 (1 - 2), 131 - 161." type="journal article" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="56254B06335AFFC5FE6EF8B8FCB6F8FB" author="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wytwer, J." box="[503,812,1862,1888]" pageId="11" pageNumber="430" pagination="511 - 514" refId="ref8414" refString="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wytwer, J. (2004) The South American millipede genus Phaneromerium Verhoeff, 1941, with the description of a new cavernicolous species from Brazil (Diplopoda: Polydesmida: Fuhrmannodesmidae). Annales Zoologici, 54 (3), 511 - 514. [https: // www. researchgate. net / publication / 233589098 _ The _ South _ American _ millipede _ genus _ Phaneromerium _ Verhoeff _ 1941 _ with _ the _ description _ of _ a _ new _ cavernicolous _ species _ from _ Brazil _ Diplopoda _ Polydesmida _ Fuhrmannodesmidae]" type="journal article" year="2004">Golovatch &amp; Wytwer 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
